IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE ORGANIZATION SUPPORTS LOCAL FEEDING PROGRAMS THROUGHOUT WASHTENAW COUNTY THROUGH THE COLLECTION AND DELIVERY OF SURPLUS PERISHABLE FOOD FROM LOCAL SOURCES AND FROM THE ACQUISITION AND DISTRIBUTION OF FOOD THROUGH A NATIONAL FOOD BANK PROGRAM.
IRS990.MissionDesc: OUR MISSION IS TO ALLEVIATE HUNGER AND ELIMINATE ITS ROOT CAUSES IN WASHTENAW COUNTY, MICHIGAN.
IRS990.Desc: THE ORGANIZATION RECEIVES DIRECT DONATIONS OF FOOD, ADMINISTERS SOME GOVERNMENT FOOD PROGRAMS (TEFAP/USDA/SUMMER FOOD PROGRAM) AND PURCHASES FOOD FROM WHOLESALERS. FOOD IS SORTED, PACKED AND DELIVERED TO MORE THAN 100 OTHER NONPROFIT AGENCIES SUCH AS HOMELESS SHELTERS, FOOD PANTRIES, LOW INCOME HOUSING AND AFTER-SCHOOL PROGRAMS, WHO THEN DISTRIBUTE THE FOOD TO PEOPLE IN NEED THROUGHOUT WASHTENAW COUNTY. IN THE LAST FISCAL YEAR, APPROXIMATELY 7.8 MILLION POUNDS OF FOOD WERE DISTRIBUTED, MORE THAN 60% OF WHICH WAS PRODUCE AND PROTEIN ITEMS. ADDITIONALLY, 83,125 IN CASH GRANTS AND 1,042,901 IN THE FORM OF CREDITS FOR FOOD PURCHASING WERE DISTRIBUTED TO PARTNER AGENCIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: FOOD GATHERERS OPERATES A COMMUNITY KITCHEN, WHICH IS LOCATED IN THE ROBERT J. DELONIS CENTER, HOME OF THE SHELTER ASSOCIATION OF WASHTENAW COUNTY. VOLUNTEERS TRANSFORM RESCUED AND BULK FOOD INTO USEFUL FOOD RESOURCES AND PREPARE AND SERVE APPROXIMATELY 12 MEALS PER WEEK TO THOSE IN NEED.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: SUMMER FOOD SERVICE PROGRAM - THE SUMMER FOOD SERVICE PROGRAM (SFSP) WAS CREATED TO ENSURE THAT CHILDREN IN LOWER-INCOME AREAS COULD CONTINUE TO RECEIVE NUTRITIOUS MEALS DURING LONG SCHOOL VACATIONS WHEN THEY DO NOT HAVE ACCESS TO THE NATIONAL SCHOOL LUNCH OR SCHOOL BREAKFAST PROGRAMS. THE SFSP IS A PROGRAM OF THE UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE, WHICH PROVIDES FUNDING TO COVER THE COSTS OF THE MEALS AT ELIGIBLE SITES. FOOD GATHERERS IS THE LARGEST SPONSOR OF THE SFSP FOR CHILDREN IN WASHTENAW COUNTY. FREE MEALS ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO CHILDREN UNDER 18 YEARS OF AGE AND UNDER OR PERSONS UP TO AGE 26 WHO ARE ENROLLED IN AN EDUCATIONAL PROGRAM FOR THE MENTALLY OR PHYSICALLY DISABLED THAT IS RECOGNIZED BY A STATE OR LOCAL PUBLIC EDUCATIONAL AGENCY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE I, PAGE 1, PART I, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THREE KINDS OF GRANTS MAY BE PROVIDED TO PARTNER ORGANIZATIONS: DIRECT CASH GRANTS, GRANTS TO PURCHASE NEW EQUIPMENT AND CREDITS THAT MAY BE APPLIED TO VERIFIED FOOD PURCHASES. CASH GRANTS: PARTNER ORGANIZATIONS MAY RECEIVE CASH GRANTS TO HELP SUPPORT STAFFING AND OTHER INFRASTRUCTURE COSTS TO KEEP THEIR PANTRIES RUNNING. NEW EQUIPMENT GRANTS: GRANTS OF NEW EQUIPMENT MAY BE MADE TO PARTNER ORGANIZATIONS TO SUPPORT FOOD PANTRY OPERATIONS. EQUIPMENT MAY INCLUDE SUCH ITEMS AS REFRIGERATORS AND FREEZERS. CREDITS FOR FOOD PURCHASES: EACH YEAR, PARTNER ORGANIZATIONS MAY RECEIVE PURCHASE CREDITS FOR FOOD. THESE ARE AWARDED EACH QUARTER BASED ON DEMONSTRATED NEED AND MAY BE USED ONLY TO COVER THE COST OF FOOD AND FOOD- RELATED SUPPLIES SUCH AS BAGS AND PACKAGING MATERIALS. INTERNSHIPS: WE OFFER PAID, SHORT-TERM INTERNSHIPS TO QUALIFIED UNIVERSITY STUDENTS TO ASSIST IN THE ADMINISTRATION OF OUR SUMMER FOOD PROGRAM. THESE INTERNS RECEIVE A SET AMOUNT OF MONEY EACH MONTH FOR THE DURATION OF THE PROGRAM.
IN FY2023, WE HAD 3,399 UNIQUE VOLUNTEERS WHO WORKED A TOTAL OF 48,121.50 HOURS.
THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE PRESIDENT/CEO, STAFF, AND MEMBERS OF THE FINANCE COMMITTEE BEFORE IT GOES TO THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

THE ORGANIZATION MONITORS AND ENFORCES ITS CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY BY PROVIDING ALL BOARD MEMBERS WITH A COPY OF THE POLICY ON AN ANNUAL BASIS AND REQUIRING ALL BOARD MEMBERS TO CERTIFY IN WRITING THAT THEY HAVE REVIEWED THE POLICY AND ARE FREE OF CONFLICTS OR HAVE DISCLOSED THE CONFLICT TO THE BOARD.
COMPENSATION FOR THE PRESIDENT AND CEO IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED ANNUALLY BY THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS.
THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
